responded: The bug is in the following code in `src/wast-parser.cc`:

```c++
3481|       std::unique_ptr<Module> m;
3482|       std::unique_ptr<WastLexer> lexer = WastLexer::CreateBufferLexer(
3483|           filename, qsm->data.data(), qsm->data.size(), &errors);
3484|       ParseWatModule(lexer.get(), &m, &errors, options_);
...
3493|       *module = std::move(*m.get());
```

If `ParseWatModule` fails, `m` will be `nullptr`, and dereferencing `*m.get()` will cause a null pointer dereference.

**Patch plan:**  
Add a check to ensure `m` is not null before dereferencing. If `m` is null, handle the error gracefully (e.g., return an error or skip assignment).

Let's generate the patch.

args.patch:
--- a/src/wast-parser.cc
+++ b/src/wast-parser.cc
@@ -3481,16 +3481,21 @@
       std::unique_ptr<Module> m;
       std::unique_ptr<WastLexer> lexer = WastLexer::CreateBufferLexer(
           filename, qsm->data.data(), qsm->data.size(), &errors);
       ParseWatModule(lexer.get(), &m, &errors, options_);
       for (const auto& error : errors) {
         if (error.loc.offset == kInvalidOffset) {
           Error(qsm->loc, "error in quoted module: %s", error.message.c_str());
         } else {
           Error(qsm->loc, "error in quoted module: @0x%08" PRIzx ": %s",
                 error.loc.offset, error.message.c_str());
         }
       }
-      *module = std::move(*m.get());
+      if (m) {
+        *module = std::move(*m.get());
+      } else {
+        Error(qsm->loc, "failed to parse quoted module: module is null");
+        return Result::Error;
+      }
       *out_command = std::move(command);
       break;
   }
